# maps-geo / deck.gl

deck.gl renders large-scale geospatial data on the GPU (WebGL2 via luma.gl) in a
browser. For deterministic headless output we author a `Deck` instance with a fixed
`initialViewState` + static `layers`, render it in headless Chromium, wait for
`onAfterRender`, and screenshot the canvas to a PNG. Freeze the view
(`controller:false`), bundle all data, and skip basemap tiles to keep output
byte-stable.

controls do
  maps-geo.title: { label: "Map title", type: "text" }
  maps-geo.layer_spec: { label: "Layer spec (JS)", type: "textarea", file: "src/layers.js" }
  maps-geo.longitude: { label: "Center longitude", type: "text" }
  maps-geo.latitude: { label: "Center latitude", type: "text" }
  maps-geo.zoom: { label: "Zoom", type: "range" }
  maps-geo.width: { label: "Width (px)", type: "text" }
  maps-geo.height: { label: "Height (px)", type: "text" }
end

## Required reading
- deck.gl docs — https://deck.gl/docs (vis.gl / OpenJS, MIT)
- Deck class API — https://deck.gl/docs/api-reference/core/deck (MIT)
- SnapshotTestRunner headless render+capture — https://deck.gl/docs/api-reference/test-utils/snapshot-test-runner (MIT)
- Capture canvas as image codepen — https://codepen.io/Pessimistress/pen/ExyyzjV (Xiaoji Chen, MIT)
- No official Anthropic/Claude skill — https://github.com/anthropics/skills

## Render
```bash
npm install @deck.gl/core @deck.gl/layers puppeteer
# index.html builds a Deck with controller:false + onAfterRender → window.__done
# render.js launches headless Chromium with swiftshader and screenshots the canvas
node render.js   # writes out/map.png
```

## Failure modes
- Empty/black canvas in headless macOS/CI: launch Chromium with `--use-gl=swiftshader` (no real GPU).
- Non-deterministic output: a basemap (Mapbox/MapLibre/CARTO) fetches tiles + needs tokens — drop the basemap or pre-bundle static tiles.
- Captured too early: screenshot before `onAfterRender` → blank frame. Always `waitForFunction('window.__done')`.
- Animations/transitions on a layer break byte-stability — disable them and set `controller:false`.
- No native Node-GL renderer; Node WebGL1 was dropped — you must use a real browser.
